cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.FL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper is focused on temporal logics and their decidability and tractability properties. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with pushdown automata and their model-checking against temporal logics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of temporal logics for specifying and verifying the behavior of reactive systems. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with context-free properties and their combination with real-time temporal logics. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the practical applications of the proposed logics for the verification of real-time systems.
